FBIS3-17531 "drsov059_a_94006" FBIS-SOV-94-059 Document Type:Daily Report 28 Mar 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Agreement Reached on Baykonur Leasing Terms LD2803154194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1456 GMT 28 Mar 94 LD2803154194 Moscow ITAR-TASS Language: English Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Ivan Ivanov and Anna Melnikova] [Text] Moscow March 28 TASS -- Russia and Kazakhstan agreed on Monday that Russia will lease the Baykonur space launching site for 20 years with a further prolongation for 10 years and will pay 115 U.S. million dollars a year. A corresponding agreement was signed today by Presidents Boris Yeltsin and Nursultan Nazarbayev. Baykonur will be under the Russian sovereignty and jurisdiction, which means that Russians working there will abide by Russian laws. The Russian military-space forces will continue to run the space launching site, according to the agreement.
